items.title: Zunino's 2 HRs power Mariners past Rangers
items.summary: Mike Zunino hit two home runs and the Mariners jumped back in front of the Rangers in the American League Wild Card standings with an 8-1 victory at Globe Life Park on Wednesday.

items.title: Marisnick departs with injured right thumb
items.summary: Jake Marisnick departed Wednesday's game against the Angels with an injury right thumb after sliding into second base, trying to stretch a single into a double. He was thrown out and left the game shortly thereafter.
